"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-new-twist-in-olympic-row-as-government-backs-pradhan-panel-62-81.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, Aug 13: The dispute surrounding the Nepal Olympic Committee (NOC) has taken a new turn.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 62, \"end\": 85, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nepal Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 87, \"end\": 90, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the NOC led by Jeevan Ram Shrestha continues to operate with international recognition, the government has approved the formation of a new ad-hoc NOC committee coordinated by former president Dhruv Bahadur Pradhan.\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 124, \"end\": 127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 135, \"end\": 154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeevan_Ram_Shrestha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeevan Ram Shrestha\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeevan_Ram_Shrestha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeevan_Ram_Shrestha\"}, {\"begin\": 266, \"end\": 269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 318, \"end\": 325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maharaja\", \"score\": 0.995133787650352, \"rank\": 0.004889411579305082, \"text\": \"Bahadur\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maharaja\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maharaja\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few days ago, Minister for Youth and Sports Teju Lal Chaudhary, during a briefing at the ministry, had announced that an ad-hoc NOC committee would be formed with the consent of 22 national sports associations.\", \"from\": 336, \"to\": 548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 382, \"end\": 400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teju_Lal_Chaudhary\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teju Lal Chaudhary\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teju_Lal_Chaudhary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teju_Lal_Chaudhary\"}, {\"begin\": 466, \"end\": 469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The National Sports Council (NSC), chaired by Minister Chaudhary, had earlier declared the NOC under Shrestha's leadership unconstitutional.\", \"from\": 550, \"to\": 690, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Sports_Council\", \"score\": 0.9999931095122537, \"rank\": 6.883786627103543e-06, \"text\": \"National Sports Council\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Sports_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Sports_Council\"}, {\"begin\": 579, \"end\": 582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_National_Security_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.102035335030773e-16, \"text\": \"NSC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_National_Security_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_National_Security_Council\"}, {\"begin\": 641, \"end\": 644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The formation of the new ad-hoc committee has now added complexity to the NOC dispute in Nepal.\", \"from\": 691, \"to\": 786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 765, \"end\": 768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 780, \"end\": 785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal\", \"score\": 0.9999999556198428, \"rank\": 4.43800830713394e-08, \"text\": \"Nepal\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to a statement issued today by the new committee's spokesperson, Samim Miya Ansari, Pradhan's ad-hoc committee consists of nine members.\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 863, \"end\": 880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salim_Miya_Ansari\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Samim Miya Ansari\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salim_Miya_Ansari\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salim_Miya_Ansari\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ansari said that the remaining members and other subcommittees would be made public at a press conference to be held on August 17 at the NOC office in Satdobato.\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 1096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 935, \"end\": 941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mohammad_Hamid_Ansari\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.020965510713174e-19, \"text\": \"Ansari\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mohammad_Hamid_Ansari\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mohammad_Hamid_Ansari\"}, {\"begin\": 1072, \"end\": 1075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have not revealed all names yet.\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We will provide full details at the press briefing,\\\" he said, adding, \\\"For now, we have only announced the coordinator and my name.\\\"\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement read, \\\"On August 10, 2025, a joint meeting of presidents, general secretaries, and officials from 23 sports associations affiliated with the Nepal Olympic Committee decided to form a nine-member ad-hoc committee under the chairmanship of Hon.\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1424, \"end\": 1447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nepal Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dhruv Bahadur Pradhan, the outgoing and honorary president of the Nepal Olympic Committee.\\\"\", \"from\": 1526, \"to\": 1617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1532, \"end\": 1539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maharaja\", \"score\": 0.995133787650352, \"rank\": 0.004889411579305082, \"text\": \"Bahadur\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maharaja\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maharaja\"}, {\"begin\": 1592, \"end\": 1615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nepal Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The recent chapter of the NOC dispute began after a special general assembly and election were held under Shrestha's leadership last year in defiance of a court order.\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1645, \"end\": 1648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1725, \"end\": 1733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shrestha\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On December 3, by amending the NOC statute at the special general assembly in defiance of the Patan High Court's order, Shrestha paved the way for himself to serve a third term as president.\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1977, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1818, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1881, \"end\": 1886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patan_district\", \"score\": 0.9999906713877332, \"rank\": 8.583029081681593e-06, \"text\": \"Patan\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patan_district\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patan_district\"}, {\"begin\": 1887, \"end\": 1897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/High_Court_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.9828185055636678, \"rank\": 0.005570294997524042, \"text\": \"High Court\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/High_Court_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/High_Court_of_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1907, \"end\": 1915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shrestha\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Previously, the statute allowed only two terms.\", \"from\": 1978, \"to\": 2025, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shrestha was then elected for the third time based on the amended statute.\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2027, \"end\": 2035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shrestha\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the NOC, the election was held online despite a Supreme Court order to halt it.\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2119, \"end\": 2122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2163, \"end\": 2176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supreme_Court_of_India\", \"score\": 0.9999584292691666, \"rank\": 3.848144454441004e-05, \"text\": \"Supreme Court\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supreme_Court_of_India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supreme_Court_of_India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following this, the NSC declared the NOC's special general assembly and election invalid.\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2216, \"end\": 2219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_National_Security_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.102035335030773e-16, \"text\": \"NSC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_National_Security_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_National_Security_Council\"}, {\"begin\": 2233, \"end\": 2236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, with government approval, an ad-hoc committee has been formed under Pradhan, who has served multiple terms as both NOC general secretary and president.\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2442, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2406, \"end\": 2409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During Shrestha's two terms as general secretary, Pradhan was president.\", \"from\": 2444, \"to\": 2516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2451, \"end\": 2459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shrestha\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shresthas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After his second term, Pradhan left the NOC and was later named honorary president.\", \"from\": 2517, \"to\": 2600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2557, \"end\": 2560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9994308142648364, \"rank\": 0.0005694314742517014, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pradhan, also president of the Nepal Gymnastics Association and a former Inspector General of Nepal Police, is currently a federal lawmaker from the Rastriya Prajatantra Party.\", \"from\": 2601, \"to\": 2777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2632, \"end\": 2637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal\", \"score\": 0.9999999556198428, \"rank\": 4.43800830713394e-08, \"text\": \"Nepal\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nepal\"}, {\"begin\": 2638, \"end\": 2648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.9998719437638877, \"rank\": 0.00012806908914315574, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastic